sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K311004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Complement of Ethanolamine Utilization Microcompartment proteins from Salmonella LT2
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Three proteins subunits of a bacterial micro-compartment. The genes are in the pSB1C3 plasmid. A total of 5 micro-compartment genes are cloned in a single plasmid. They are arranged as two sets of two genes (in a single operon) with one gene which is upstream to the pairs. They are flanked directly upstream by a mutated Lac promoter to make them constitutively expressed. The genes were amplified by PCR from genomic DNA using primers that would introduce restriction sites flanking the genes.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The genes were amplified by PCR from genomic DNA using primers that would introduce restriction sites flanking the genes. The genes were ligated into a modified pUC biobrick vector containing a constitutive promoter. The genes were taking in their native operons and ligated sequential according to size.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Matthew Adams, Swati Choudhary, Anthony Goering, Rachel Farr, Ethan Johnson, Annie Kathuria, Poonam Srivastava, Ian Windsor
